nd personal injury for their addictive features.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>How Meta’s Threads Became as Popular as X</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/05/technology/threads-meta-twitter-x.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/05/technology/threads-meta-twitter-x.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/05/technology/threads-meta-twitter-x.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The social platform that Meta once positioned as a rival to Elon Musk’s X now has 500 million monthly users. It increasingly resembles Reddit.</description><dc:creator>Eli Tan</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 09:01:42 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Meta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Threads</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Instagram</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Facebook</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mark E Zuckerberg</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">X</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/30/multimedia/META-THREADS-1-03-tgph/META-THREADS-1-03-tgph-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Ian C. Bates for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>“We want to be the largest and best platform for public conversation,” said Connor Hayes, the head of Threads. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Intel Benefits From a New Shift in A.I. Spending</title><link>https://www.nytim